Object.Field:
Schedule this scenario hourly with 4 repetitions every 15 minutes. The Scenario will provide itself to raise an error if it is already running
Execute this script on the desired Schema (Default is INT_STD but you can choose NICIM or EPMASTER).
Change the Logical Schema property according to the Physical Schema (Default is ORACLE_INTERFACCIA but you can change it to ORACLE_NICIM or ORACLE_EPMASTER) in these objects:
A. WAIT FOR DATA
B. ORACLE_START_SCENERY 1. Set Start Value (Source and Target Command) 2. Execute Scenery (Source Command) 3. Set End Value (Target Command)
TEST Script:
CREATE TABLE ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION ( "SCEN_NAME" VARCHAR2(200 BYTE) NOT NULL ENABLE, "SCEN_VERSION" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT '001' NOT NULL ENABLE, "CONTEXT" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT 'TEST' NOT NULL ENABLE, "AGENT_CODE" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT 'AGENT' NOT NULL ENABLE, "FLG_EXEC" NUMBER(*,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL ENABLE, "STATUS" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT 'Waiting for update' NOT NULL ENABLE, "PRIORITY" NUMBER(*,0) DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL ENABLE, "SYNC_MODE" NUMBER(*,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL ENABLE, "START_DATE" DATE, "END_DATE" DATE, CONSTRAINT "ODI_SCENERY_EXECUTION_PK" PRIMARY KEY ("SCEN_NAME", "SCEN_VERSION", "CONTEXT", "AGENT_CODE"));
PROD Script:
CREATE TABLE ETL_SCENERY_EXECUTION ( "SCEN_NAME" VARCHAR2(200 BYTE) NOT NULL ENABLE, "SCEN_VERSION" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT '001' NOT NULL ENABLE, "CONTEXT" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT 'PROD' NOT NULL ENABLE, "AGENT_CODE" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT 'AGENT' NOT NULL ENABLE, "FLG_EXEC" NUMBER(*,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL ENABLE, "STATUS" VARCHAR2(35 BYTE) DEFAULT 'Waiting for update' NOT NULL ENABLE, "PRIORITY" NUMBER(*,0) DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL ENABLE, "SYNC_MODE" NUMBER(*,0) DEFAULT 1 NOT NULL ENABLE, "START_DATE" DATE, "END_DATE" DATE, CONSTRAINT "ODI_SCENERY_EXECUTION_PK" PRIMARY KEY ("SCEN_NAME", "SCEN_VERSION", "CONTEXT", "AGENT_CODE"));
Synchronization mode of the scenario:
1 - Synchronous mode (default). The execution of the calling session is blocked until the scenario finishes its execution.
2 - Asynchronous mode. The execution of the calling session continues independently from the return of the called scenario.
